In [[telecommunication]], an '''address message''' is a [[message]] sent in the forward direction that contains (a) [[address]] [[information]], (b) the [[signaling]] information required to [[route]] and connect a [[call]] to the called [[telephone line|line]], (c) service-class information, (d) information relating to [[user]] and [[telecommunications network|network]] facilities, and (e) call-originator identity or call-receiver identity.

'''Source:''' from [[w:Federal Standard 1037C]]